Well,partner I take exception first of all to your condescending attitude and secondly denigrating the actions of the warriors who served.<br>
I have never asked anything from my gov't except for the freedom for which I fought and 58,000 died for.<br>
Your comparisons of the dead from the Civil War and WW2 are ludicrous.  Neither war lasted ten years and neither had some many Americans serve in combat. <br>
If you had taken the time to read some of these posts on these sites, you won't find any of us asking for anything.<br>
Well, maybe one thing, recognition for our deeds. I personally, don't have any inadquacies.  I am not leading a &quot;no direction life&quot; nor do I feel &quot;cheated&quot;.  I have worked for the same company for 28 years and have been married to the same woman for 27 years.<br>
I am trying to stay calm but to paint all Vietnam vets with a brush as broad as the one that you are using is inviting some really nasty replies.<br>
I did not ever look for the &quot;euphoria&quot; that my father recieved upon his return for Europe.  And by the way,  what the hell is wrong with a parade to welcome home warriors?<br>
You are an idiot and probably a noload REMF.  It could be nastier but I don't bother with idiots who make general statements to stire the pot as it were. 
